From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v46 - PS4 Liverpool ATOM/IIO/dp_clock diagnostics

Five parallel research agents (Opus, Hermes, GLM, Kimi, DeepSeek — captured
under research/ideas/2026-05-10-*.md) analyzed the v42/v43 dark-screen logs
and converged on the same blocker: `amdgpu_atom_execute_table()` returns 0
for AdjustDisplayPll, the kernel falls back to `mode->clock`, but the
resulting GPU programming produces no live DP signal — the bridge times out
on lane-lock and the monitor stays dark.

The agents disagree on *why* ATOM returns 0:
  - Opus:    GPU register state is wrong when ATOM runs.
  - Hermes / GLM: 6.x dropped `ioreg_read/write` callbacks; if PS4 VBIOS uses
                  ATOM IIO opcodes they now hit the wrong path (MMIO instead
                  of PCI I/O BAR).
  - Kimi:    `dp_clock` is being zeroed *upstream* of ATOM by a failed DPCD
             read (lost ddc adapter in 6.x connector init), and ATOM dutifully
             returns 0 when fed usPixelClock=0.
  - DeepSeek: PPLL writes need a reset/lock sequence — but self-flags as
              likely wrong (memory ps4_6x_v45_pll_writes_drop already proved
              those mmDCCG_PLL banks don't store on Liverpool).

Goal of v46: stop guessing. Bundle the cheapest data-gathering pieces from
Opus + Hermes + GLM, add Kimi's two-line defensive `dp_clock` floor (zero
cost if wrong, fixes the screen if right). Skip DeepSeek entirely. One boot
disambiguates four of five hypotheses.

Four instrumentation points (no behavior change beyond Kimi's floor):

  1. atombios_crtc.c::amdgpu_atombios_crtc_adjust_pll v3 case
     - Capture `ret` from amdgpu_atom_execute_table (currently discarded)
     - Print usPixelClock, ucTransmitterID, ucEncodeMode, ucDispPllConfig,
       ucExtTransmitterID, dp_clock BEFORE the call
     - Print ret, ulDispPllFreq, ucRefDiv, ucPostDiv AFTER the call
     - Gated on CHIP_LIVERPOOL || CHIP_GLADIUS — no-op on other ASICs

  2. atombios_crtc.c::amdgpu_atombios_crtc_program_pll
     - Capture `ret` from the SetPixelClock execute_table call
     - Print enter line with frev, crev, crtc_id, clock, pll_id, ref_div,
       fb_div, frac_fb_div, post_div, encoder_id, encoder_mode, bpc,
       ss_enabled
     - Tells us whether the *second* ATOM call (downstream of
       AdjustDisplayPll) is reaching the hardware.

  3. atom.c::atom_iio_execute (ATOM_IIO_READ / ATOM_IIO_WRITE)
     - pr_info_once on first IIO opcode of either kind
     - Definitively tells us whether Starsha2-018 uses ATOM indirect I/O
     - If it does: GLM/Hermes I/O BAR restoration is the next iteration
     - If it doesn't: IIO hypothesis killed, focus on register-state (Opus)
       or dp_clock (Kimi)

  4. ps4_bridge.c::ps4_bridge_detect (Kimi Change B — defensive write)
     - After amdgpu_atombios_dp_get_dpcd, force
         dp_clock      = 270000  (2.7 Gbps)
         dp_lane_count = 4
     - PS4 internal DP -> MN864729 link is hardwired at 4 lanes @ 2.7 Gbps
       regardless of DPCD. If the DPCD read silently failed, this restores
       the correct link config; if DPCD succeeded, this overwrites with the
       same correct values. No downside on Liverpool.

What the next boot tells us (read UART log):
  - "ps4_atom: ATOM indirect I/O path used" line appears
       -> GLM/Hermes IIO hypothesis confirmed; restore rio_mem + ioreg_read/
          write next iteration.
  - No IIO line, AdjustDisplayPll OUT freq=148500, screen lights up
       -> Kimi was right; promote dp_clock floor permanent.
  - No IIO line, OUT freq=148500, screen still dark
       -> ATOM healthy; failure downstream in DP TX or bridge lock. Pivot to
          dumping DIG/DP-TX state and bridge 0x60f8/0x60f9 lane status.
  - No IIO line, OUT freq=0 with non-zero input dp_clock
       -> VBIOS table runs but takes "no output" branch under 6.x register
          state. Opus crashniels golden-register port; or amdgpu.atom_debug=1.
  - r=-EINVAL (or other negative)
       -> Bytecode aborted. Add amdgpu.atom_debug=1 for opcode trace.
  - "SetPixelClock OUT r=" non-zero or absent
       -> Second ATOM call is the actual blocker. Trace
          amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll and DP TX programming.

This patch keeps the v44 PPLL dump (0019), v45 manual programmer (0020),
v40 IRQ9/ACPI fix, and v42 no-skip-ATOM all active. Visibility-only addition,
plus the one defensive write in ps4_bridge.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atom.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atom.c
@@ -118,10 +118,19 @@
 			base++;
 			break;
 		case ATOM_IIO_READ:
+			/* v46: confirm whether VBIOS uses ATOM indirect-I/O
+			 * opcodes at all. 6.x routes IIO via reg_read (MMIO);
+			 * 5.4 routed it via ioreg_read (PCI I/O BAR). If this
+			 * fires on Liverpool/Gladius, restoring the I/O BAR
+			 * path is the next iteration's fix. */
+			pr_info_once("amdgpu_atom_iio: first IIO_READ reg=0x%x (6.x routes via reg_read; 5.4 used ioreg_read)\n",
+				     CU16(base + 1));
 			temp = ctx->card->reg_read(ctx->card, CU16(base + 1));
 			base += 3;
 			break;
 		case ATOM_IIO_WRITE:
+			pr_info_once("amdgpu_atom_iio: first IIO_WRITE reg=0x%x val=0x%x (6.x routes via reg_write; 5.4 used ioreg_write)\n",
+				     CU16(base + 1), temp);
 			ctx->card->reg_write(ctx->card, CU16(base + 1), temp);
 			base += 3;
 			break;
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_crtc.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/atombios_crtc.c
@@ -427,8 +427,29 @@
 			else
 				args.v3.sInput.ucExtTransmitterID = 0;

-			amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context,
-					   index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
+			/* v46: Liverpool/Gladius diagnostic — capture ret + in/out
+			 * of the AdjustDisplayPll ATOM call. Helps disambiguate
+			 * whether the table aborts (-EINVAL), runs but writes
+			 * zero, or runs and writes a real freq. */
+			if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL ||
+			    adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+				pr_info("ps4_atom: AdjustDisplayPll v1.3 IN pix=%u tx=0x%02x enc=%u cfg=0x%02x ext_tx=0x%02x dp_clock=%u\n",
+					le16_to_cpu(args.v3.sInput.usPixelClock) * 10,
+					args.v3.sInput.ucTransmitterID,
+					args.v3.sInput.ucEncodeMode,
+					args.v3.sInput.ucDispPllConfig,
+					args.v3.sInput.ucExtTransmitterID,
+					dp_clock);
+			{
+				int r = amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context,
+						   index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
+				if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL ||
+				    adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+					pr_info("ps4_atom: AdjustDisplayPll v1.3 OUT r=%d freq=%u ref=%u post=%u\n",
+						r, le32_to_cpu(args.v3.sOutput.ulDispPllFreq) * 10,
+						args.v3.sOutput.ucRefDiv,
+						args.v3.sOutput.ucPostDiv);
+			}
 			adjusted_clock = le32_to_cpu(args.v3.sOutput.ulDispPllFreq) * 10;
 			if (args.v3.sOutput.ucRefDiv) {
 				amdgpu_crtc->pll_flags |= AMDGPU_PLL_USE_FRAC_FB_DIV;
@@ -740,7 +761,19 @@
 		return;
 	}

-	amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
+	/* v46: Liverpool/Gladius diagnostic — capture ret of SetPixelClock
+	 * ATOM call (the second ATOM call in the modeset path; downstream of
+	 * AdjustDisplayPll). If this returns non-zero or never runs, the
+	 * actual blocker is here, not in AdjustDisplayPll. */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+		pr_info("ps4_atom: SetPixelClock IN frev=%u crev=%u crtc=%u clock=%u pll=%u ref=%u fb=%u frac=%u post=%u enc_id=%u enc_mode=%u bpc=%d ss=%d\n",
+			frev, crev, crtc_id, clock, pll_id, ref_div, fb_div,
+			frac_fb_div, post_div, encoder_id, encoder_mode, bpc, ss_enabled);
+	{
+		int r = amdgpu_atom_execute_table(adev->mode_info.atom_context, index, (uint32_t *)&args, sizeof(args));
+		if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS)
+			pr_info("ps4_atom: SetPixelClock OUT r=%d\n", r);
+	}
 }

 int amdgpu_atombios_crtc_prepare_pll(struct drm_crtc *crtc,
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/ps4_bridge.c
@@ -737,6 +737,15 @@

 	amdgpu_dig_connector->dp_sink_type = CONNECTOR_OBJECT_ID_DISPLAYPORT;
 	amdgpu_atombios_dp_get_dpcd(amdgpu_connector);
+	/* v46 (Kimi hypothesis): PS4 internal DP→MN864729 link is fixed at
+	 * 4 lanes @ 2.7 Gbps. If amdgpu_atombios_dp_get_dpcd silently fails
+	 * (lost ddc adapter in 6.x connector init), dp_clock would stay 0
+	 * and AdjustDisplayPll would be fed usPixelClock=0, returning 0.
+	 * Force the known-good PS4 link config so the ATOM input is sane. */
+	pr_info("ps4_bridge_detect: forcing dp_clock=270000 dp_lane_count=4 (was %d/%d)\n",
+		amdgpu_dig_connector->dp_clock, amdgpu_dig_connector->dp_lane_count);
+	amdgpu_dig_connector->dp_clock = 270000;
+	amdgpu_dig_connector->dp_lane_count = 4;

 	mutex_lock(&mn_bridge->mutex);
 	cq_init(&mn_bridge->cq, 4);
